!pape.response: /announce Paper Mario for the Nintendo 64 is a very painful game to reset due to a 22 minute segment at the beginning where nothing happens. Generally if a run dies after Speedy Spin is acquired, that's it for the day and we figure out something else to do. If a run dies before Speedy Spin ... we may reset, but it depends on how I'm feeling that day

!mwsf.response: At the end of August (26-28), I'll be doing a Paper Mario Rando for Midwest Speedfest. In the meantime I'll be practicing a decent bit and figuring out what kind of settings to use for the event! The full schedule: https://oengus.io/en-GB/marathon/mwsf2022/schedule

!schedule.response: /announce Monday-Friday on days that I stream will be speedruns of whatever game I feel like playing that day (or channel point requests). Saturday and Sunday are guaranteed to be rando's, whether it's Paper Mario or something else, we will be doing at least one rando. Streams generally will start between 2-3PM Pacific.
